Figure 2. FTIR spectra of a free-standing PEDOT/PSS film before (red dotted line) and after (solid line) $1 \mathrm{M} \mathrm{KOH}$ treatment.

It is well known that acid treatment can enhance the electrical conductivity of PEDOT [11,12,26,27]. This is mainly attributed to the removal of the insulating PSS $^{-}$and the morphological change of the film. In this study, we firstly compared the film absorption in the UV range of four samples: PEDOT/PSS without any additional treatment (PH1000), $\mathrm{PEDOT} / \mathrm{PSS}$ treated with $\mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{SO}_{4}\left(\mathrm{PH} 1000 \rightarrow \mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{SO}_{4}\right)$, PEDOT/PSS treated with EG $\left(\mathrm{PH} 1000 \rightarrow\right.$ EG), and PEDOT/PSS treated with EG and $\mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{SO}_{4}(\mathrm{PH} 1000$ $\rightarrow \mathrm{EG} \rightarrow \mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{SO}_{4}$ ). This experiment was conducted using the same film with an alignment mark to avoid the effect of film thickness on the absorbance measurement. As shown in Figure 3a, after $\mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{SO}_{4}$ treatment, the absorption of PEDOT/PSS at $225 \mathrm{~nm}$ decreased suggesting the removal of the insulating PSS $^{-}$, whereas, the electrical conductivity significantly increased to ca. $2000 \mathrm{~S} / \mathrm{cm}$ (Table 1). A similar tendency was observed in the EG treated films. In Figure 3b, after EG treatment, the absorption of PEDOT/PSS decreased and the electrical conductivity increased to ca. $1000 \mathrm{~S} / \mathrm{cm}$. Interestingly, when we further treated this film using $\mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{SO}_{4}$, the absorption in the UV range did not show a significant change, suggesting the amount of $\mathrm{PSS}^{-}$remained constant. On the other hand, the electrical conductivity further increased to ca. $2000 \mathrm{~S} / \mathrm{cm}$, which was almost identical to the film treated with $\mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{SO}_{4}\left(\mathrm{PH} 1000 \rightarrow \mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{SO}_{4}\right)$. These results suggest that, besides the removal of the insulating PSS $^{-}$, the treatment of $\mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{SO}_{4}$ also enhanced the electrical conductivity of the films.\\
